x4freetext: The 3.2 MV PELLETRON Accelerator of the
Research Laboratory for Nuclear Reactors at the Tokyo
Lithium evaporated on copper target was
bombarded by 1.5 nsec bunched proton beam.
.For neutron energies 8-90 keV proton energy is 1.903
MeV (22 keV above threshold energy of P-Li7 reaction),
pulse  repetition rate 2 MHz, average proton current
energies proton BEAM energy is 2.0, 2.1, 2.3 and MeV,
pulse repetition rate 4 MHz, average proton current
w/o Pb plate  with Pb plate
Measurements with Tc, blank and Au samples were
made cyclically to average out changes in experimental
rays. Main detector 15.2 cm diameter by 20.3 cm long
was centered  in a 33.0 cm outer diameter by 35.6 cm
resolution is 7% at 0.662 MeV and time resolution is
4.0 ns for 0.511 MeV gamma. The distance between
sample and surface of main detector is 86 cm.
Li-6 glass detectors were used for neutron flux
monitoring. 5 mm diameter * 5 mm length 6-Li detector
located 30 cm away from neutron source was used for
8-90 keV region, the same detector  located 50 cm away
from neutron source - for 190-keV region, 102 mm
diameter * 6.4 mm length detector located 300 cm away
from neutron source was used for 330 keV region, and,
finally, the same detector located 460 cm away from
.Gold sample for monitor, metallic, chemical purity
.Technetium sample - oxide powder Tc-O2 scaled in an
aluminium case (20 mm inner diam, 30 mm outer diam,
